node.text:
Just a quick reminder: changing room you is NOT the real you. 

One would assume that by making changing room lights and mirrors super flattering, big retailers would sell more because we would feel like our best selves in the new garments. But most just throw harsh fluorescent overhead lights in a claustrophobic and way too hot tiny box that has dust bunnies lying around, and the curtain doesn’t close properly, so everyone can see you half naked. 

So let’s just keep it in mind that the image the mirror shows is distorted, unrealistic, and isn’t how we EVER look outside of these torture chambers.

💪🏻
Via @lainey.molnar
